for making the python code as a command in linux environment use the code below


-------------------------------------------------------------
execute this code in command shell
chmod +x weather.py


-------------------------------------------------------------

And now add the python code to the environment variable PATH
use the code ~/.bashrc to open environment editor and """you can use nano ~/.bashrc to open also"""
with using this code 
export PATH="$PATH:~/bin """ replace bin with the weather.py script directory"""


***********************************************************************************************************
for the C file you can use the command bellow to compile it 
gcc -o findfile findfile.c

and if gcc wasn't installed use
""" sudo apt install gcc """
to install gcc compiler


